-- Greece's Piraeus Bank posts Q2 profit, beats forecast
-- 
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 10:41AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, Aug 29 (Reuters) - Greece's second-largest lender by assets Piraeus Bank <BOPr.AT> reported a profit in the second quarter as lower funding costs boosted its net interest income.

Piraeus on Friday posted a profit of 164 million euros ($216 million). Analysts polled by Reuters expected the bank to report a loss of 133 million euros on average.